    <string name="weather_about_air">The air quality index describes how polluted the air currently is.  It is derived from the concentrations of pollutants such as carbon monoxide, nitrogen dioxide, sulphur dioxide, ozone, and particulate matter.  The higher the value, the greater the potential for adverse health effects.</string>
    <string name="weather_ultraviolet_description_1">Low danger from UV rays for the average person.  No protection needed; you can safely stay outside.</string>
    <string name="weather_ultraviolet_description_2">Moderate risk of harm from unprotected sun exposure.  Seek shade during midday hours, and wear sunscreen, a hat, and sunglasses.</string>
    <string name="weather_ultraviolet_description_3">High risk of harm.  Reduce time in the sun from 10 AM to 4 PM.  Apply sunscreen and wear protective clothing, a hat, and sunglasses.</string>
    <string name="weather_ultraviolet_description_4">Very high risk of harm.  Minimize sun exposure during midday hours.  Protection against skin and eye damage is essential.</string>
    <string name="weather_ultraviolet_description_5">Extreme risk of harm.  Avoid the sun during midday hours.  Unprotected skin can burn in minutes.</string>
